st want to play ksp2\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"The Space Peacock","CreatedById":224498,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-12-21T19:20:45Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224350023\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022221659\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221703186374\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022226446\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Krzysztof Jaromir\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nJust now, Krzysztof Jaromir said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMight be its own bug report, but there\u0027s a similar issue, but instead of eating, you have to drink\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nyou can also replicate it in the same way, just instead its getting thirsty.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nluckily there\u0027s a simple workaround for this: hook yourself up to IV fluids\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"dandoesstuff","CreatedById":223454,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-12-21T19:20:47Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis bug report got me hungry\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Anth","CreatedById":161238,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-12-21T19:21:08Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhat? This is true?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis is a concern.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Sir Eskomaz","CreatedById":222560,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-12-21T19:21:10Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDon\u0027t forget the sleep bug\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224350023\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022221659\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221703186374\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022226446\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Krzysztof Jaromir\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nJust now, Krzysztof Jaromir said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMight be its own bug report, but there\u0027s a similar issue, but instead of eating, you have to drink\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nyou can also replicate it in the same way, just instead its getting thirsty.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"The Space Peacock","CreatedById":224498,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-12-21T19:24:58Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224350028\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022221659\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221703186470\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022222560\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Sir Eskomaz\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 minutes ago, Sir Eskomaz said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDon\u0027t forget the sleep bug\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nsee, now that\u0027s just a skill issue\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Sir Eskomaz","CreatedById":222560,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-12-21T19:26:41Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224350029\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022221659\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221703186698\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022224498\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022The Space Peacock\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nJust now, The Space Peacock said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nsee, now that\u0027s just a skill issue\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003E:KerbalKerbnoooooo:\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Spork Witch","CreatedById":221879,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-12-21T19:30:38Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nRegarding root cause, this seems more like a metabolism issue, rather than a digestion issue.\u00A0 If we can freeze the metabolism, there\u0027d be no need for snacks or digestion!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"WhereAreTheBathrooms","CreatedById":167730,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-12-21T19:37:33Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis is actually a problem with most games, it\u0027s a limitation of how the hunger system works, devs can only do so much unfortunately. I\u0027ve found having a really good setup is the only way around it, by incorporating an IV drip into your gaming rig you can have a\u00A0 constant feed which sates your hunger while you play. But it\u0027s a shame this kind of thing is so innaccessible due to the cost. It also requires you to give up flavour, but I haven\u0027t found that to be an issue when the trade-off is playing KSP non-stop. Seems like an easy choice to me.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Mr. Fusion","CreatedById":20005,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-12-21T19:40:21Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTried to look into it more, but reproducibility is screwy - always happens but at varied triggers and intervals. Either dependent on complex state or possibly a firmware issue. What\u0027s worse is the digestive system does not seem to have proper API documentation, overall very sloppy implementation tbh\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Gargamel","CreatedById":64714,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-12-21T19:51:00Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf you tip well and leave the door unlocked, Ubereats will deliver to your desk. \u00A0 \u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"MARL_Mk1","CreatedById":192535,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-12-21T20:34:16Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m refunding until this get fixed. I was able to tolerate No Man\u0027s Sky and Cyberpunk 2077 at launch, but this is outrageous. Will make sure to not recommend the game until this is looked upon.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"PicoSpace","CreatedById":224964,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-12-21T20:34:31Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWait\u2026 you guys DON\u2019T have a giant stack of snacks taking up 1/2 of your desk space?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAmateurs\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022;)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_wink.gif\u0022 title=\u0022;)\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Royalswissarmyknife","CreatedById":216092,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-12-21T20:42:22Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224350028\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022221659\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221703186470\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022222560\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Sir Eskomaz\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, Sir Eskomaz said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDon\u0027t forget the sleep bug\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat bug can easily be fixed with enough coffee.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Scarecrow71","CreatedById":210112,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-12-21T20:46:05Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI think having to go to sleep, or having to go to work, might be related to this bug.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Darrin H","CreatedById":228817,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-12-21T21:14:50Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003E\nGotta give credit to the original finder of this issue:\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u003Cimg class=\u0022ipsImage ipsImage_thumbnailed\u0022 data-fileid=\u00221182\u0022 data-ratio=\u002221.76\u0022 data-unique=\u00227aiyhtxf7\u0022 width=\u0022533\u0022 alt=\u0022image.png\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/monthly_2023_12/image.png.8898c2f9c35852933abb9d7351889185.png\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"The Space Peacock","CreatedById":224498,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-12-21T21:24:39Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224350082\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022221659\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221703191565\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022210112\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Scarecrow71\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n37 minutes ago, Scarecrow71 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI think having to go to sleep, or having to go to work, might be related to this bug.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nthats an interesting proposition, i\u0027ll have to test that \u003Cimg alt=\u0022;)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_wink.gif\u0022 title=\u0022;)\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Dakota","CreatedById":225122,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-12-21T21:30:23Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-gramm=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224350082\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022221659\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221703191565\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022210112\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Scarecrow71\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n43 minutes ago, Scarecrow71 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents ipsClearfix\u0022 data-gramm=\u0022false\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI think having to go to sleep, or having to go to work, might be related to this bug.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYeah I\u0027m definitely experiencing having to go to work preventing me from playing the game. Devs pls fix\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"modus","CreatedById":207631,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-12-21T21:40:19Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224350080\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022221659\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221703191342\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022216092\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Royalswissarmyknife\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n57 minutes ago, Royalswissarmyknife said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat bug can easily be fixed with enough coffee.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat causes the pp bug\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Superpluto126","CreatedById":206953,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-12-21T23:21:11Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis bug is so irritating, that\u0027s over a dozen minutes less playtime!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Deddly","CreatedById":62955,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-12-22T06:46:11Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSee this is why KSP 1 will always be better than KSP 2. In KSP 1, they solved this issue early on by implementing no timewarp during burns. Together with ion engines, all the bugs mentioned here were solved. Why can\u0027t the KSP 2 devs learn from things that were already fixed a \u003Cem\u003Edecade\u003C/em\u003E ago?\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:huh:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_undecided.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:huh:\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Davidian1024","CreatedById":210190,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-12-22T14:39:03Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://soylent.com/\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://soylent.com/\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"jclovis3","CreatedById":188635,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-12-22T22:53:11Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSolution (as seen at the end of videos before the release of KSP2):\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDuring sleep or work hours, find a long transit between CBs and after completing your burn, turn off your monitor and do not bother with time warp.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDuring meal hours, play as normal and do not time warp as you orbit around a CB getting in position for your next burn. Just step away long enough to prepare said mean and come back. Eat while watching the game so you can interact when necessary and then resume eating. It\u0027s like eating while you watch TV, only better because you get to be\u00A0 a part of the show.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBathroom break? Commit to a long burn and go pee. If you feel the burn, grab some water on your way back.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224350280\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022221659\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221703227571\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002262955\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Deddly\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n16 hours ago, Deddly said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSee this is why KSP 1 will always be better than KSP 2. In KSP 1, they solved this issue early on by implementing no timewarp during burns. Together with ion engines, all the bugs mentioned here were solved. Why can\u0027t the KSP 2 devs learn from things that were already fixed a \u003Cem\u003Edecade\u003C/em\u003E ago?\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:huh:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_undecided.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:huh:\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIn KSP1, you can time warp up to 4x in the physics warp. You just hold right-alt when you tap that first key to begin warp, and every increment or decrement greater than 1x would be in a physics enabled time warp. In KSP2, this is similar to the physics time warp you get while in atmosphere. With KSP1, this kind of time warp enabled slow turning ships to turn more rapidly. You could also change your thrust during a physics enabled time warp. Wish they\u0027d bring that back for KSP2.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222023-12-22T22:57:38Z\u0022 title=\u002212/22/2023 10:57  PM\u0022 data-short=\u0022Dec 22\u0022\u003EDecember 22, 2023\u003C/time\u003E by jclovis3\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003EAdded text.\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"}]}